<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="241" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/4927: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-10T00:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 10, 1919,
                                        midnight.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received May
                                    10, 7.52 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>2073. Your 1888, May 7. I approve of your suggestion to detail either
                            Halstead or Coffin, preferably the latter, as successor to Coolidge in
                            Vienna. The detail should be made without delay. Lansing.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>